# Uzen fork

Uzen is the first hardfork after Shasta on Taiko L2. It is timestamp-activated and, on the EVM side, inherits Ethereum's **Osaka** spec. This page captures the protocol-level changes on top of Shasta — each item applies equally to every execution client (alethia-reth, taiko-geth, …).

## Overview

- **Baseline**: Shasta.
- **Activation**: timestamp-based, configured per network.
- **EVM spec**: Osaka (Pectra + Prague + Osaka behavior, where inherited).
- **Transaction policy**: blob transactions (EIP-4844, type 3) are **not supported** and must be rejected at both the mempool and block-inclusion layers.

## ZK Gas

Uzen introduces a second, independent gas meter ("zk gas") that runs alongside the normal EVM gas meter. It approximates the cost of generating a ZK proof for a block and is what ultimately bounds per-block zk-complexity.

**Spec (source of truth):** [zk_gas_](https://github.com/taikoxyz/taiko-mono/blob/main/packages/protocol/docs/zk_gas_spec.md)[spec.md](http://spec.md) — defines the per-opcode costs, per-transaction limit, per-block limit, and overflow semantics.

Behavior summary:

- Pre-Uzen blocks: zk metering is a no-op.
- Uzen and later: every executed opcode is charged against the zk gas meter. Exceeding the per-tx limit aborts the transaction; exceeding the per-block limit stops block-building / fails block validation.

## Block header shape

Uzen pins several header fields to fixed values so block hashes are reproducible:

- `parent_beacon_block_root` — pinned to zero.
- `requests_hash` — set to the empty requests hash (no Prague-style requests list is carried).
- `blob_gas_used` / `excess_blob_gas` — pinned to zero, consistent with the "no blob transactions" policy.

The blob-gas and requests-hash pinning match [op-reth](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/tree/develop/rust/op-reth): its block assembler sets `(blob_gas_used, excess_blob_gas) = (Some(0), Some(0))` once Ecotone is active and `requests_hash = Some(EMPTY_REQUESTS_HASH)` once Isthmus is active — same convention Uzen adopts.

The `parent_beacon_block_root = 0` pinning is **Uzen-specific**. OP Stack carries the real L1 beacon block root in this field (propagated from the payload sidecar), and exposes it (by `STATICCALL` the EIP-4788 contract at `0x000F3df6D732807Ef1319fB7B8bB8522d0Beac02`, like Ethereum L1) to L2 contracts. Uzen doesn't use EIP-4788 and fixes the field at zero for reproducibility.

## EVM block context

Two EVM-level values need explicit rules under Uzen because the normal post-merge derivations don't apply:

- **`BLOBBASEFEE` opcode** — will always returns **1 wei**. With `excess_blob_gas` pinned to zero, the EIP-4844 fake-exponential formula gives the 1-wei minimum; Uzen defaults to 1 when no excess-blob-gas is present so the opcode never returns zero or undefined. This matches [op-reth](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/tree/develop/rust/op-reth), which also hardcodes `BlobExcessGasAndPrice { excess_blob_gas: 0, blob_gasprice: 1 }` in the EVM block env when Cancun is active — a well-trodden path for rollups that don't carry real blob state.